2016/hochwaldpfad.title: Hochwaldpfad
2016/hochwaldpfad.text: This nice afternoon hike took us through thick and pristine forests and through the beautiful Wahnbachtal near Weiskirchen. It passes through an extended forest area at the border between the states of Rheinland-Pfalz and Saarland, which is home to wild cats. We did this tour in winter, however I expect this to be particularly nice in spring time.

2014/panoramatrail.title: Panorama Trail
2014/panoramatrail.text: This hike ranks among the most spectacular one-day hikes we have ever done. The vantage point alone is breath-taking: Glacier Point, a peak high above Yosemite valley provides the perfect view over Yosemite valley, its water falls, Half-Dome as well as the Sierra Nevada. From there the trail starts and leads us around the rim of the mountains, passing by several spectacular waterfalls, viewpoints and through pine tree forests. The climax of the day is Nevada Fall, where we stand by the edge, watching the water fall down into the valley. We arrive Yosemite valley at sunset.

2011/wageten.title: Wageten
2011/wageten.text: This was my first hike in the Zurich area after I moved to Switzerland. At the same time, it was my first mountain hike whatsoever. It turned out that we had chosen a perfect autumn day to climb the Wageten in the Glarner Alps. We had left early in the morning and we quickly broke through the low cloud layer, finding a sunny mountain area. We hiked to the Wageten, descending via the so-called Wageten gap down to the Oberurnertal. This descend turned out to be quite difficult, since in October there was already fresh snow on the very steep path. Nevertheless, we made it to the valley, taking the cable car down to Oberurnen.

2011/planggenstock.title: Planggenstock
2011/planggenstock.text: A beautiful hike to the northernmost peak of the Glarner Alps. We started our hike late, so we took a cable car to the high valley of Oberurnen, saving about 2 1/2 hours. This is a beautiful hike for early autumn, when higher areas may already be covered in snow. The summit of Planggenstock provides a nice view over the Linth valley.

2012/dreibuendenstein.title: Dreibündenstein
2012/dreibuendenstein.text: This was our very first snow shoe hike in a beautiful area around Chur in Graubünden. The summit plateau offers really great views of the surrounding Alpine panorama.

2012/sihlsprung.title: Sihlsprung
2012/sihlsprung.text: If you are tired of snow and ice, early spring comes with limited options for hikes in the area south of Zurich. A nice option is a hike along the valley of the Sihl valley. Here, already in March the signs of spring cannot be overlooked. At the Sihlsprung, the river Sihl passes a narrow canyon, resulting in rapids, narrows and cascades. The trail leads along the river, through the gorge before passing through open grassland, forests and farmland.

2012/laegeren.title: Lägeren
2012/laegeren.text: The ridge trail across the Lägeren mountain is probably one of the most Alpine hikes that you can find in the immediate surrounding of Zürich. The mountain hiking trail passes the ridge and is rather narrow and exposed. In some places, you will need to use your hands. This is a very rewarding experience, that can be combined with a visit of the castle Regensberg as well as the old town of Baden.

2012/innerthal.title: Innerthal
2012/innerthal.text: On this hike, nothing went as we had planned. We first learned that due to a landslide, the trail to the summit of Gross Aubrig, which we wanted to climb originally, was blocked. The alternative route around the summit was marked so badly that we lost the trail multiple times. In addition to missing markers and an invisible path, thick fog and rain made navigation complicated. We could only find our way via GPS, passing through steep, slippery and pathless terrain. After more than 20 kilometers we arrived in Vorderthal just in time to catch the last bus back to Zurich.

2012/federispitz.title: Federispitz
2012/federispitz.text: This was one of the most strenuous hikes I did so far in the Zurich country. The first part of the trail is comparably easy to walk, while the final climb up to the summit and the ridge between the first summit (Vorderer Federispitz) and the main summit of Federispitz requires stamina and sure-footedness. However, the effort is rewarded by a phantastic view over the Walensee, Lake Zurich and the Alps.

2013/hasliberg.title: Hasliberg
2013/hasliberg.text: We did this memorable snow shoe hike in the area around Meiringen on a weekend trip to the Bernese Alps. Hasliberg offers great opportunities for all kinds of wintersport, including winter hiking, snow shoe hiking, and skiing.

2013/adlisberg.title: Adlisberg
2013/adlisberg.text: This was a short afternoon hike on a group event, organized by our research group. Starting in downtown Zürich, the trail took us across Adlisberg, ending in a restaurant near Hottingen.

2013/stanserhorn.title: Stanserhorn
2013/stanserhorn.text: Another beautiful autumn hike, this time in the area of Lucerne. We start in Dallenwil, where we take a cable car up to Wiesenberg. From there, a trail leads us through forests and meadows up to Stanserhorn. The spacious and extended summit area offers us nice panoramas of Lake Lucerne, the adacent valleys as well as the surrounding Alps. From the summit, a cable car takes us down to Stans.

2014/hummel.title: Hummel
2014/hummel.text: We ended doing this tour early in spring, when the snow had already melted in Zurich. It turned out that the snow in the Einsiedeln area was still high and this turned out to be an extremely difficult hike without snowshoes.

2014/mostelberg.title: Mostelberg
2014/mostelberg.text: We did this as a quick afternoon hike on a group event organized by our research group. The hike starts at the summit station of the Mostelberg cable car. Despite being easily accessible, on a clear day you will nevertheless see great mountain panoramas. One section of the trail offers also great views onto Lauerzersee.

2014/kloental.title: Klöntal
2014/kloental.text: On a sunny and warm sunday in autumn, we decided to explore the Kloental valley, which is hidden in the Glarner Alps. Arriving from Zurich by train, we took the Postbus from Netstal to the Kloental valley. When we started, the colorful trees were glowing in full sunshine. However, shady trails soon led us along the southern shore of the lake. We enjoyed nice vistas of the lake and the surrounding mountains, before hiking down through a forest to Netstal, where we took the train back to Zurich.

2015/albiskette.title: Alsbiskette
2015/albiskette.text: With a height of 869 meters, Uetliberg is the house mountain of the city of Zurich: a perfect region for a quick hiking or, at least in winter, sledging trip on the weekend. This winter, we wanted to hike across the ridge of the Albiskette, a chain of low mountains along the southeastern shore of Lake Zurich. The first part of the trail leads along slippery stairs down from the summit of Uetliberg. The following part leads to forests and along open farmland to Felsenegg. From here, we took a cable car down to the station of Adliswil.

2015/rigi.title: Rigi
2015/rigi.text: On dull winter days with low-hanging clouds obscuring the sun, it is a good idea to flee to the mountains. On such a day, we traveled to Lake Lucern, where wanted to do a winter hike at the famous Rigi mountain. Notably, the country around Rigi provides several kilometers of winter hiking trails, i.e., specially prepared snow trails that are easy to walk even without snow shoes. Our choice of the day was rewarded with a spectacular sunset at the summit. The low cloud cover was beautifully illuminated by the setting sun, and mountain peaks were protruding from the clouds like small islands.

2015/sihlwald.title: Sihlwald
2015/sihlwald.text: A relaxing hike, passing first through the Wildnispark Lagnau, featuring wolves, bears, lynxes and many other wild animals. The second half of the hike leads through the Sihlwald, a natural reserve just at the footstep of the city of Zurich.

2015/rotenfluh.title: Winter Hike Rotenfluh
2015/rotenfluh.text: A nice hike in the area of Grosser and Kleiner Mythen. The trail offers amazing views over Lake Lucerne and the Glarner Alps. We did this as a winter hike on prepared winter hiking trails.

2015/etzl.title: Etzl
2015/etzl.text: A beautiful but strenuous hike up to the summit of Etzl in the canton of Schwyz. The most strenuous part are the first few kilometers up to the summit, climbing up more than 800 meters, the last 300 meters of which lead via a stair with more than 500 steps. The summit provides a unique view over the Linth valley, Lake Zurich, Greifensee, Rapperswil, the Glarner Alps, the Mythen mountains as well as the Sihlsee. From the summit on, the last kilometers are easy to walk. On the final kilometers, the trail leads through an interesting peat bog, an area which reminded me a lot of Scotland.

2015/tuerlersee.title: Türlersee
2015/tuerlersee.text: We did this as a short afternoon hike, following up a short boat tour on Türlersee. This is a very easy and short circle around the lake, but the southernmost section provides great views of the Alps. Especially in spring, there is plenty of flowers around.

2015/sentiermartel.title: Sentier Martel
2015/sentiermartel.text: This was a difficult full-day hiking tour deep in the Gorges du Verdon, Europe's biggest canyon. The canyon walls are up to 700 meters high and there is no escape route on the way. This makes it absolutely necessary to inform yourself about the weather forecast, as the path can be dangerous in thunderstorms. Some sections of the trail are exposed to height, but the hiker is rewarded by grand landscapes and nature all around.

2015/mythen.title: Grosser Mythen
2015/mythen.text: The hike up to the Grosser Mythen, a well-known mountain in the country around Zurich and Zug, is a classic tour. On sunny summer days, hundreds of hikers make their way up to the summit plateau at 1899 m. The pronounced summit provides a great overview of Lake Lucerne, the Alpthal, Rigi, and the surrounding Alpine panorama. The path is steep but not particularly strenuous. It is very nicely prepared and maintained, with only a few exposed sections.

2015/roggenstock.title: Roggenstock
2015/roggenstock.text: Located at the southern end of Sihlsee, the Hoch-Ybrig area provides more than hundred kilometers of phantastic hiking trails. One of them is the geological hike to the Roggenstock, a 1770m mountain in the heart of the Hoch-Ybrig country. This trail offers beautiful sights of geological formations, which often look as if they were straight from the set of a phantasy movie. We started our trail close to the Seeblisee. We then first hiked up to the summit of Roggenstock, continuing to our goal in Oberiberg, from where we took the bus back to Zurich.

2015/altberg.title: Altberg
2015/altberg.text: An afternoon tour from Rütihof across the summit of Gubrist to the Altberg and back again. This is great tour for a sunny autumn day, when the woods are in full color and mushrooms are plenty.

2015/leistchamm.title: Leistchamm
2015/leistchamm.text: This hike to the summit of Leistchamm leads to a cliff with a spectacular view over the Glarner Alps and Walensee, which lies about 1700m deeper. Note that the last part of this hike leads through rough terrain that can be rather difficult and dangerous to walk after rainfall. As you can see on the pictures, first snow falls can already be expected in October.

2015/mattstock.title: Mattstock
2015/mattstock.text: On an unusally warm November day, we climbed the summit of Mattstock close to the village of Amden. Our hike starts at the chairlift station Niederschlag, from where we take the long route up to Mattstock. This trail offers scenic views of the Glarner Alps and Walensee. The final ascend leads us through impressive structures, which help to protect the village of Amden from avalanches. We finally take a break at the summit, before we take the shorter, direct route back to Amden.

2016/fronalpstock.title: Fronalpstock
2016/fronalpstock.text: A short snow shoe hike from the station of the Stoos funicular to the summit of Fronalpstock. From the summit, you will have a great view onto Lake Lucerne and the surrounding mountains.

2016/eglisau.title: Wine trail Eglisau
2016/eglisau.text: This hike along the so-called wine trail starts in the small and picturesque town of Eglisau. Eglisau is beautifully located at the banks of the river Rhine. The mild climate and the slopes of the gorges of the Rhine make it a good place for the production of wine. Not surpringly, the first part of the trail passes through wineyards, before it follows a small path along the banks of the Rhine, where numerous traces of beavers can be found. Finally, the path leaves the banks of the Rhine and climbs up to the village of Buchberg, from where it leads us back to Eglisau.

2016/rothenturm.title: Moorpfad
2016/rothenturm.text: This hike leads through one of Switzerland's largest and ecologically most important bog areas close to Rothenturm, Schwyz. Starting at the railway station of Biberbrugg, a forest trail first leads us through shady woods, before it reaches the small river Biber. Following its banks for a while, the path eventually crosses an extended wetland area, with bog pools, typical moor vegetation, and traces of past peat production. The path arrives in the small town of Rothenturm, from where we took the train back to Zurich.

2016/tuefelschilen.title: Tüfels Chilen and Schauenberg
2016/tuefelschilen.text: Since I didn't know the area around Winterthur well, I didn't have much expectations when we started this hike. And to my big surprise, this turned out to be one of the top hikes in the area around Zurich. Starting in the village of Kollbrunn, the trail first leads through a fairy-like forest and along a picturesque small creek. After about one hour, it reaches Tüfels Chilen, a water cascade with spectacular stone terraces overgrown with moss. The trail continues along innumerable small cascades and a few bigger waterfalls, the so-called 'Giessen'. After around two and a half hours, we finally reach the summit of Schauenberg, a small mountain that is home to an old castle ruin and that can easily remind you of the Weathertop. The path finally descends through quiet and picturesque villages and along another creek towards the station of Rämismühle, from where we take a train back to Zurich.

2016/cimetta.title: Cimetta
2016/cimetta.text: When winter returns to Zurich in spring, it is a good idea to flee to Ticino for a day. On a Sunday in April, we did exactly this, leaving for Locarno in the morning and returning in the evening. Half a day at Lago Maggiore is plenty of time for a short hike in the Carmada-Cimetta country just above the city. The short trail from Carmada to the summit of Cimetta provides breathtaking views over Lago Maggiore, the towns of Locarno and Ascona, as well as the surrounding Alps. The start point in Carmada is particularly easy to reach via a funicular and a cable car directly from the main station of Locarno.

2016/chatzensee.title: Chatzensee
2016/chatzensee.text: A sunday afternoon tour from Höngg, across Hönggerberg to Chatzensee in Affoltern. On the way to the lake, we pass by the ruins of castle Alt-Regensberg, an abandoned castle situation on a small hill. Around Chatzensee you can find extended bog and protected swamps, with chances to see rare birds and animals.

2016/5lakehike.title: Five Lake hike
2016/5lakehike.text: As of July 2016, this was easily the most beautiful hike we've done in Switzerland. This trail is a Swiss classic. It passes by five mountain lakes and offers spectacular panoramic views on the surrounding Alps. When we did the hike in mid July 2016, there was still fresh snow which just fell a few days ago. This makes the hike more strenous than usual, and some portions can become dangerously slippery. Good mountain shoes are a must!

2016/oberblegisee.title: Oberblegisee
2016/oberblegisee.text: A hike from Braunwald to Oberblegisee, a magical place in a secluded valley in the Glarner Alps. The hike crosses the Bösb&auml:chital, a picturesque mountain valley with a small stream. In summer, the lake Oberblegisee is a great place for wild swimming.

2016/gulmen.title: Gulmen
2016/gulmen.text: Having enjoyed two very nice hikes to Mattstock and Leistchamm in late 2015, we decided to return to the Amden area close to Walensee for another autumn hike. This time our stating point is Arvenbühl and we take a route via the summit of Gulmen to Amden, from where we took the bus back to Ziegelbrücke station. We enjoyed a sunny, golden October day, with spectacular views towards the rugged Glarner Alps, the Toggenburg and the Säntis massif.

2016/hundwileren.title: Hundwileren
2016/hundwileren.text: This was a short afternoon hike in the Einsiedeln area. The viewpoint on Hundwileren provides a nice overview of Einsiedeln, the Rothenturm moorland and the Sihlsee. The hike directly starts at the main station of Einsiedeln and returns to there via the monastery.

2017/flumserberg.title: Flumserberg
2017/flumserberg.text: In the area around and above Flums you can find plenty of winter hiking trails embedded in a scenic Alpine landscape, with particularly spectacular views towards the Walensee and Churfirsten mountain ridge. On a sunny January sunday we went up to Maschgenkamm by cable car. From there, a nicely prepared network of winter hiking trails leads via Panüöl to Fursch, at the foot of the Spitzmeilen. We took the same route back, returning via Maschgenkamm by cable car.

2017/irchel.title: Irchel
2017/irchel.text: This was a short hiking tour on an overcast and foggy day in the Rhine area. We started near Teufen, where the river T¨ss meets the Rhine. Passing by trees cut down by beavers, we ascend to Irchel Hochwacht, where we just break through the low cloud layer. Through foggy forests, we descend to Tssegg from where we return to Zurich.

2017/gumen.title: Gumen
2017/gumen.text: A hike on prepared winter hiking trails in the area of Braunwald, which is a paradise for mountain lovers in any season. From Grotzenbühl we follow a trail to Ortstockhaus, and then onward to the summit of Gumen.

2017/rigi.title: Rigi
2017/rigi.text: A great winter hike on a sunny day along prepared winter hiking trails. We started this tour at the summit station of Rigi Scheidegg, which can be reached via train and cablecar from Arth. From Scheidegg we follow the mountain ridge towards Rigi Staffel and finally Rigi Kulm.

2017/waldstaetterweg.title: Waldstätterweg: Vitznau to Brunnen
2017/waldstaetterweg.text: This hike is one stage of the long distance hiking trail Waldstätterweg, which leads around Lake Lucerne in seven days.

2017/thurwies.title: Thurwies
2017/thurwies.text: Having hiked to the estuary of the river Thur at Thurspitz earlier this year, this summer we wanted to visit the Thur source at the foot of Säntis mountain. What a beautiful place! The young Thur falls down the rocks in an impressive cascade, and meanders through the picturesque valley. It crosses a gorge and forms spectacular waterfalls, before reaching the village of Unterwasser. A great area to spent time on a hut summer day, with numerous spots to relax by the refreshing river.

2017/benjislaketrail.title: Benjies Lake Trail
2017/benjislaketrail.text: A short walk through the woods to Benjis Lake.

2017/mcintoshbrooktrail.title: McIntosh Brook Trail
2017/mcintoshbrooktrail.text: A short walk through a forest to the cascades of McIntosh Brook

2017/micahilltrail.title: Mica Hill Trail
2017/micahilltrail.text: A hike through beautiful moorland to a hill covered with glittering mica. From here we enjoyed a great view towards the Atlantic Ocean.

2017/skylinetrail.title: Skyline Trail
2017/skylinetrail.text: One of the most famous hikes of Cape Breton National Park.

2017/friherrenberg.title: Friherrenberg
2017/friherrenberg.text: A short afternoon hike in the area of Einsiedeln with great views of the Alps

2018/rigi.title: Rigi
2018/rigi.text: A short but steep winter hike on prepared winter hiking trails leading up to the summit of Rigi.

2018/bettmeralp.title: Bettmeralp
2018/bettmeralp.text: A winter hike in the Aletsch arena in Wallis.

2018/rotenfluh.title: Rotenfluh
2018/rotenfluh.text: A spontaneous test tour on cross blades, a mix between snow shoes and cross-country skis.

2018/walensee.title: Walensee Nordufer
2018/walensee.text: This is a perfect tour for early spring, when there is still snow in the mountains. The north shore of Walensee is blessed by a very mild climate and springtime arrives early. A highlight of this tour is a visit of the Seerenbachfälle, Switzerland's highest waterfall with a total height of 585 meters.

2018/swisspath1.title: Waldstätterweg: Flüelen - Brunnen
2018/swisspath1.text: This hike is the third stage of the trail Weg der Schweiz. It is also one stage of the long distance hiking trail Waldstätterweg, which leads around Lake Lucerne in seven days.

2018/swisspath2.title: Waldstätterweg: Seelisberg - Flüelen
2018/swisspath2.text: This hike is the second stage of the trail Weg der Schweiz. It is also one stage of the long distance hiking trail Waldstätterweg, which leads around Lake Lucerne in seven days.

2018/nesslau.title: Thurweg: Nesslau - Wattwil
2018/nesslau.text: A great hike along the long distance hiking trail Thurweg, which leads from the source to the mouth of the river Thur. On this stage, we pass many cascades, river gorges, and beautiful forests.

2018/faelensee.title: Fälensee
2018/faelensee.text: A hike to the fjord-like Fälensee in the Alpstein area. This is a particularly impressive tour in early spring, as it starts right near the so-called flower alps, which you will find covered in colorful mountain flowers in early spring.

2018/oeschinensee.title: Oeschinensee
2018/oeschinensee.text: A hike around the Oeschinensee near Kandersteg in the Bernese Alps. The Oeschinensee easily ranks among Switzerland's most beautiful lakes. It is surrounded by the impressive panorama of the Bernese Alps.

2018/mythen.title: Grosser Mythen
2018/mythen.text: A hike to the summit of famous Grosser Mythen in the Schwyzer Alps. Due to its remarkable shape, Grosser Mythen is also sometimes called the Matterhorn of Schwyz. The winding and relatively easy mountain trail up to the summit offers truly spectacular views.

2018/klosterfahr.title: Kloster Fahr
2018/klosterfahr.text: A short afternoon walk to Kloster Fahr monastery, returning to Zurich via the valley of the river Limmat.

2018/reppischtal.title: Reppischtal
2018/reppischtal.text: A short afternoon walk in the woods close to Zurich.

2018/saentis.title: Säntis
2018/saentis.text: A demanding mountain hike up to the highest peak in the Alpstein massif.

2018/braunwald.title: Braunwald Panorama Trail
2018/braunwald.text: A perfect hike for sunny autumn days with colorful trees.

2018/fessisseeli.title: Fessis Seeli
2018/fessisseeli.text: Spectacular hike in the Unesco World Heritage area Sardona, on a beautiful autumn day.

2018/hummel.title: Hummel
2018/hummel.text: A short Sunday afternoon hike with great views of Sihlsee and Einsiedeln.

2018/sihlbrugg.title: Hirzl Höchli
2018/sihlbrugg.text: A very short but beautiful afternoon stroll along paved roads near Hirzl.

2019/flumserberg.title: Flumserberg
2019/flumserberg.text: Hiking in winter wonderland in the area of Flums.

2019/hohenstein.title: Hohenstein
2019/hohenstein.text: A short afternoon hike in the Uetliberg area.

2019/schaffhausen.title: Schaffhausen
2019/schaffhausen.text: This easy hike led us along one stage of the long distance hiking trail Via Rhenana. As a particular highlight, the trail passes by the famous rhinefall of Schaffhausen, one of Europe's largest waterfalls by volume.

2019/vitznau.title: Waldstätterweg: Küssnacht to Vitznau
2019/vitznau.text: A day hike through the Riviera of Lake Lucerne south of the Rigi massif. Due to the mild climate at the south face of Rigi, this tour is a great choice for a sunny day in early spring. This hike is one stage of the long distance hiking trail Waldstätterweg, which leads around Lake Lucerne in seven days.

2019/sihlwald.title: Sihlwald
2019/sihlwald.text: An afternoon hike from Sihlwald up to the ridge of the Albis mountains near Zurich.

2019/alpenpanorama.title: Alpenpanoramaweg Einsiedeln
2019/alpenpanorama.text: This hike is a long day tour following the Alpenpanoramaweg from Lachen via Stöcklichrüz to Einsiedeln. The first two hours are pretty steep and exhausting, while the rest of the tour is quite relaxed but long.

2019/fischingen.title: Kloster Fischingen
2019/fischingen.text: This hike from Fischingen monastery via St. Iddaburg and Grat back to Fischingen is a great tour for early spring, when the mountains are still covered in snow.

2019/tamins.title: Senda Sursilvana: Tamins - Chur
2019/tamins.text: This was a relaxed day-hike along the young river Rhine. The path starts at castle Reichenau near the village of Tamins, passes by the impressive landslide near Felsberg and arrives at the main station of Chur.

2019/verzasca.title: Valle Verzasca
2019/verzasca.text: This is a perfect hike for hot summer days.

2019/pilatus.title: Pilatus
2019/pilatus.text: A relatively short but steep hike from Alpnachstad to the summit of Pilatus. To date, this was my hike with the largest ascend of more than 1600 meters. The reward is a grand mountain landscape around the area of Mattalp, a view of the world's steepest train track, as well as a superb summit panorama on Lake Lucerne and the surrounding Alps.

2019/regensberg.title: Regensberg
2019/regensberg.text: A short circle around the beautiful town of Regensberg, at the border of the cantons of Zurich and Aargau.

2019/seealpsee.title: Seealpsee
2019/seealpsee.text: A relaxed afternoon hike from Wasserauen to Seealpsee and back again.

2019/heckelbusch.title: Heckelbuschfelsen
2019/heckelbusch.text: A short stroll through the woods around the village of Hentern to the rock formations of Heckelbusch.

2019/egelsee.title: Egelsee
2019/egelsee.text: An afternoon hike through the enchanted beech woods around Egelsee, the largest natural lake in the canton of Aargau.

2019/glomtinden.title: Glomtinden
2019/glomtinden.text: A short hike from Rorvika to the summit of Glomtinden close to Kalle.

2019/hoven.title: Hoven
2019/hoven.text: The Hoven mountain is widely recognizable by its peculiar shape and prominence. It rises above the surrounding flat marshland like a shark fin. At its northwestern base, a beautiful but muddy hiking trail leads to the summit, where you can stand at a cliff towering high above its steep eastern rockface.

2019/unstad.title: Unstad
2019/unstad.text: From the beach of Unstad on Vestvagoya a hiking trail leads around the coast to the beach of Eggum. At first, the hike follows a broad and flat road by the sea. The trail gtes gradually narrower, steeper and more slippery until it eventually disappears in the cliffs. Several spots are very dfficult to negotiate, especially when it has rained recently and in some places a slip can potentially lead to falling over the cliff. When we met another hiker that had broken his ankle we eventually decided to turn back to Unstad.

2019/fronalpstock.title: Fronalpstock
2019/fronalpstock.text: We originally wanted to hike along the ridge trail from Kligenstock to Fronalpstock. Due to a severe storm, we shortened the tour, hiking to the summit of Fronalpstock.

2020/kyburg.title: Kyburg
2020/kyburg.text: A short afternoon hike from the medieval village and castle Kyburg, to the river Töss and the Wildpark Bruderwald. On our way back we passed a couple of small streams with nice cascades and a small waterfall.

2020/linn.title: Linn
2020/linn.text: The village of Linn in the Swiss canton of Aargau is famous for its ancient linden tree. With a height of 25 meters and a circumference of more than eleven meters it is estimated to be more than 800 years old. During a certain time every year, the tree casts its shadow onto the nearby castle of Habsburg, which is the original seat of the Habsburg dynasty that ruled Europe for hundreds of years. This trail took us from the Linn linden tree to Deierberg, through the forest and past the Linn waterfall back to the village of Linn.

2020/frauholle.title: Frau Holle
2020/frauholle.text: A hike near the village of Rheinsfeld along the picturesque small river Wadrill in the densely forested Hunsrück area in Germany. The hike passes several Beaver dams, with numerous signs of trees felled by Europe's largest rodent.

2020/klinkbachtal.title: Klinkbachtal
2020/klinkbachtal.text: The Klinkbach is an - at first glance - unspectacular small forest creek near the village of Lampaden, where I grew up. At second glance, it is rich with wildlife. It is, for instance, home to the shy black stork, which is nowadays rarely found in Europe. This hike through the river valley formed by the Klinkbach took us from Lampaden to the neihhboring villages of Schömerich and Paschel and back again to Lampaden.

2020/sihlsprung.title: Sihlsprung
2020/sihlsprung.text: A Sunday afternoon tour from Sihlbrugg along the Sihl river to Silhsprung and back. Spring is a great season for this hike, as the woods are bursting with wild garlic. The many smaller rivers and cascades along the Sihl provide great opportunities for long exposure shots, and to sit by the river and enjoy the silence.

2020/ruostel.title: Ruostel
2020/ruostel.text: This tour is a hidden gem in the area of Sihlsee. We did it on a sunny afternoon in May, starting late and not expecting much. It turned out to gain a place among our favorite tours in the area. During springtime, the trail is lined with colorful flowers, among them Enzian and Orchids. When the view is clear, the mountain panorama behind Sihlsee is impressive and the panoramic views of the Gross and Chli Aubrig mountains are great. If you start early,  tour can be combined with an ascend to the Chli Aubrig and if you do not need to return to a car, you could continue towards the Wägitalersee.

2020/bockmattli.title: Bockmattlipass
2020/bockmattli.text: This was an afternoon hike on a sunny and unusally warm Sunday in May. We started at the parking lot in Innerthal close to Wägitalersee, ascending towards Schwarzenegg and on to Bockmattlihütte. Since we started late, there was just enough time to reach Bockmattlipass, skipping the ascend of the Bockmattli summit. The final ascend to Bockmattlipass is steep but you are rewarded with great panoramic views of the Wägitalersee, Lake Zurich, and the surrounding mountains.

2020/hunnenring.title: Celtic Hillfort
2020/hunnenring.text: A short tour around the Celtic Hillfort of Otzenhausen, which was built more than 2000 years ago. With a height of ten meters and a circumference of 2.5 kilometers, the Hillfort is one of Europe's most impressive archeological sites of Celtic origin.

2020/etzlpass.title: Etzlpass
2020/etzlpass.text: A short afternoon hike from St. Meinrad's chapel at the Etzpass up to the Etzl summit. Views weren't as great as expected due to dull weather. On a clear day there's great views of Sihlsee, Lake Zurich and the Alps.
